    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting an exemplary 997-generation Carrera S, maintained to a concours standard. This specimen features the 3.8L naturally aspirated flat-six powerplant, exhibiting perfect compression across all cylinders and a pristine bore scope report. The 6-speed manual transaxle is paired with a factory-spec limited-slip differential, providing tactile feedback and mechanical precision. Equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), the chassis dynamics remain sharp with zero bushing deflection or hydraulic leaks. The exterior finish retains its factory depth and luster, free of rock chips or high-velocity road rash, while the undercarriage remains remarkably clean with no signs of thermal cycling fatigue on the exhaust headers. This is a turn-key, collector-grade vehicle for the enthusiast who demands mechanical transparency and peak performance.",
